article.headline: Princeton 57, Dartmouth 53
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Lincoln Gunn scored 17 points -- including the go-ahead 3-pointer midway through the second half -- and Princeton held on for a 57-53 win over Dartmouth on Friday night. Noah Savage added 15 points for the Tigers (4-12, 1-0 Ivy League), who won their second straight game. Alex Barnett had 20 points and 10 rebounds -- both game-highs -- to lead the Big Green (8-9, 1-2), while Marlon Sanders added 15 points. The teams traded baskets for most of the game until Princeton went ahead for good on Gunn's 3-pointer with 7:54 left to play. Dartmouth rallied late, cutting the lead to 53-50 when Sanders made two free throws with 28 seconds left. The Tigers sealed the win by making 4-of-5 free throw attempts in the closing seconds.
